subject: Re: [junit] long instead of string Re: JUnit issues
msgSnippet: ... Good to hear. ... assertNotNull compares object references, i.e. does object != null, it does not work on numbers like longVar != 0. Robert
messageBody:
On Tuesday 27 January 2004 01:22, asamyuktav wrote:
> I got the bug fixed.

Good to hear.

> Was wanting to know if assertNotNull can be used to ascertain about
> long instead of string

assertNotNull compares object references, i.e. does object != null, it
does not work on numbers like longVar != 0.

Robert
